value:
Nothing like an unfamiliar challenge
to get the blood pumping. Ah, it's
been a while...

I don't mind you going out on patrol,
but if you move too far from my side,
I can't protect you. Stay close.

Worried about our allies in the field?
I can check on them for you, as long
as the skies are clear.

It's a shame you can't fly. Then again,
I can't summon like you can. We each
have our talents.

The wind may not have a voice, but it
speaks to me all the same. Even in a
new world, it tells me a great deal.

I'm King Tibarn of Phoenicis.
Your friend $Nf
says hello.
Flying high. Let's see how far I'll soar!
I'm not done yet. Not even close.

This is why I don't fight on an empty
stomach. Hey, got anything to eat?
Wait until you see what I do with this.

I'm Tibarn. I may be a king, but don't
make a big deal of it. Fawning praise
does me no good.

It's refreshing to be out on my own,
in the thick of it. The pressures of
kingship can be stifling.$k$pIt seems I've got a little more chaos
in me than most folk. If I sit still for
too long, I start itching for a fight.$k$pWe laguz have strong instincts for
battle. And that includes kings,
no matter how civilized.$k$pZelgius of Begnion, the beorc hero
Ike... The world I came from sure
didn't lack worthy competition.$k$pSeems I won't get bored anytime
soon here, though, either. Speaking
of...we should get back to it.
うおおっ！
そらっ！
うああっ！
くそっ！
Let's get started.
I can hardly control myself!
You'll get no quarter from me.
I'm no easy mark!
I've no regrets.
はははっ！
I'm King Tibarn of Phoenicis.
Whoa! Is that how you beorc greet one another?
I can see that you're a beorc, but there's something different about you...
I always pay my debts. That's how I do things.
My people do not use weapons like yours. Those are for the beorc.
I'll never forgive you if you go and get yourself killed out there, so don't do it. Got that?
If you find yourself in a dire position, you can call on me. No matter what, I will fly to your aid.
Yeah.
What now?
I'll send 'em flying.
